<br>
There's no excuse or reason to give classes skills that are useless. It's frustrating to the player, and this should be all about fun.<br>
<br>
So I think this skill should be replaced. What with ? Well, that would be up to VI, but I do have an idea.<br>
<br>
One of our class defining abilities according to Verant is bolt spells. How about an AA skill to enhance how bolt spells work ?<br>
<br>
The skill could do something like this:<br>
- 3 levels<br>
- Each level gives a chance for the bolt spell to penetrate the target and continue on to deal damage to another target (making it a sort of linear AE, but only if you can get the mobs lined up)<br>
<br>
Another way it could work:<br>
- Again 3 levels<br>
- Each level gives it an ability to penetrate X number of targets per level<br>
<br>
Both abilities would be activated, there's times you would not want bolts penetrating targets (i.e. fighting something nearby neutral mobs, having a bolt pass through and strike one would make this skill too dangerous to consider).<br>
<br>
Another form this could take:<br>
- Multiple level skill<br>
- Each level increases the number of projectiles launched against one target<br>
- Activated skill with typical re-use timer for such skills (72-144 minutes)<br>
<br>
Basiclly a poor man's manaburn. May have potential to deal alot of damage, but it's resistable and since it's bolts, blockable. Also all our bolts are checking fire resist, so targets are limited as well.<br>
<br>
